Relay number 2 is the power pre-charge which also need to be off for 4 sec then turned on (if possible we might be able to do a test this month and there is a possibility that after 20s of this relay being on it needs to be turned back off, please have code for this commented for now until further confirmation)
Relay number 3 is the Motor Pre-charge this is same as the power pre-charge (including the potential 20s)
